provisions.content:
(a)     “Board” means the Central Board of Revenue constituted under the Central
Board of Revenue Act, 1924 (IV of 1924);
(b)     “Corporation” means the Cotton Trading Corporation of Pakistan;
(c)     “factory” means a cotton ginning factory producing staple cotton for sale;
(d)     “sale price” means the price of four hundred and fifteen rupees per maund,
inclusive of excise duty, at which staple cotton is sold by the Corporation to a
textile mill;
(e)     “staple cotton” means ginned cotton other than desi-cotton
